verbose_text: Recently IL-10 was found to be strongly associated with development of ulcerated skin lesions in L. braziliensis infection in humans, supported by data showing genetic associations for single nucleotide polymorphisms (SNPs) across the IL10 gene and evidence that the -819 C/T SNP in the IL10 promoter plays a functional role in determining binding of nuclear transcription factors and levels of IL10 gene expression [XREF_BIBR].
